Theorem: ¬ (∃ x : ℤ • ∀ y : ℤ • x ≤ y)
Proof:
  Using “Generalised De Morgan”:
    Subproof for `(∀ x : ℤ • ¬ (∀ y : ℤ • x ≤ y))`:
      For any `x`:
          ¬ (∀ y : ℤ • x ≤ y)
        =⟨ “Generalised De Morgan”, “Double negation” ⟩ 
          ∃ y : ℤ • ¬ (x ≤ y)
        ⇐⟨ “∃-Introduction” ⟩ 
          (¬ (x ≤ y))[y ≔ x + (- 2)] 
        =⟨ Substitution, “Identity of +” ⟩
          ¬ (x + 0 ≤ x + (- 2))
        =⟨ “≤-Isotonicity of +”, “Symmetry of +” ⟩
          ¬ (0 ≤ (- 2))
        =⟨ Fact `0 ≤ - 2 ≡ false` ⟩
          ¬ (false)
        =⟨ “Negation of `false`” ⟩
          true
        
